column5: Hello... Does anyone on this board know anything about Cocos lake in NW Ontario?. Our group is flying-in there this summer. Thanks ...Corey

Great fishing. Good size for the walleyes. Motors all have cracked lower units. Many submerged rocks. Outfitter not the greatest or friendlyist man. Be sure to bring you own TP, very limited supply. No Ice. Was 12 hours late flying us out. All said, we would go back regardless of bad experiences. Log on and E-mail me for other info or if you would like a map with best fishing spots.
Thanks Mike for the comeback...Will definatly write you. Have to go work but will get back to you later. Corey
